## Writing Style and Voice

When making revisions or writing content, maintain Brian's authentic voice:

-   Conversational and personal tone
-   Use contractions (don't, can't, I've, etc.)
-   Include specific details and observations
-   Some self-deprecating humor
-   Direct and matter-of-fact about difficult situations
-   Avoid overly formal or academic language
-   Keep the human, relatable quality that makes his posts engaging

**Before making revisions, reference past posts in `src/content/posts/` to understand Brian's writing style and tone.**

## Code and Technical Writing

-   Be clear and practical
-   Include relevant examples when helpful
-   Explain technical concepts in accessible terms
-   Maintain consistency with existing code patterns in the project
